Title: Entanglement Entropy of Nontrivial States
Authors: Eric Benedict and So-Young Pi
Comments: 21 pages, LaTex, 2 figures in separate file
Report-no: BU-HEP 95-13
Journal-ref: Annals Phys. 245 (1996) 209-224
\\
  We study the entanglement entropy arising from coherent states and
one--particle states. We show that it is possible to define a finite
entanglement entropy by subtracting the vacuum entropy from that of the
considered states, when the unobserved region is the same.
